      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "\n\n## 🔌 The Speaker Input Priority System\n\nWhen using **NATIVE Multi-Speaker**, you can connect specific voices to Speaker 1 (opt_narrator on the unified TTS node) , Speaker2, Speaker3... inputs on the Engine node and they will override tags!\n\n**What happens if using tags:**\n\n- `narrator` becomes Speaker 1 → uses Speaker 1 input voice\n- `[Alice]` becomes Speaker 2 → uses Speaker 2 input voice\n- `[Bob]` becomes Speaker 3 → uses Speaker 3 input voice\n- etc.\n\nSO If using \n\n## **[character]** \n\n tags in your text to switch narrators, you DON'T need to connect opt_narrator, Speaker2_voice, Speaker3_voice or speaker4_voice\n\nEither for Native or for Custom modes"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
